        "client_msg_id": "8F721CB1-7960-4ECE-B05F-88DD1C526286",
        "text": "Text laid out on a screen is also a species of diagram. The real limitation one runs into is that the conventions of our writing systems (inherited from Roman script) include a flow first from left to right, then from top to bottom, which works well for sequential structures — up to and including trees — but sucks once you have to encode a more complicated graph. And sadly, it turns out that many objects of interest in the world are best represented as more complicated graphs :\/",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
